  <title>Air Quality Monitoring System </title>
<subsection xml:id="subsec-Introduction-air">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <image source="/images/air_quality.jpg" width="40%"/>
  <p>
    Air is one of the important natural resources that helps human to live on the earth. It comprises of mixture of components combined together in the presence of the atmosphere. The air is polluted with various gases like carbon dioxide, Lead (PB), Nitrogen Oxide, Ozone (O3), sulphur dioxide, ethanol and other pollutants.  
  </p>
  <p>
    when there is no adequate forest resource in the earth, and there will be insufficient air for human and other living organisms to live on the earth. Air quality has to be properly monitored in order to control the air pollution and control the fumes due to forest fire. 
Therefore, in order to monitor the air quality this small prototype model will be helpful. This prototype will monitor the air quality and alert the user when the quality of the air reaches certain level. The sensor used here to monitor the air quality is MQ135 sensor. In gas industries MQ3 is used widely to prevent leakage of gas and also it monitors the level of gas to save the people form accidents which is caused in industries. Gas sensor is widely used in oil industries to prevent the gas leakage 
  </p>
</subsection>
