  <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-gas-sensor">
    <title>Gas sensor</title>
    <p>
      Gas sensor detects the gas which is present in the atmosphere.  There are four different types of gas sensor. Each sensor has its own unique feature. In this experiment MQ135 is used to detect the air quality. This type of gas sensor will work based on the sensing material which is present inside the sensor. There will be comparator for adjusting the particular value of gas, when the gas concentration exceeds the threshold, the digital pin will be set to high. Analog pin will be used for measuring the concentration of the gas. Each sensor detects different types of gas. The table 4.1.4 explains each sensor and its own characteristics. Here MQ135 is used to detect the air quality. The sensor has three pins 5V, GND and A0 pin. Operating voltage for the sensor is 2.5V to 5V. The figure depicts the picture of MQ135 sensor and table 4.1.3 explains the pin configuration about the sensor which is described with its purpose. Fig 4.1.2 displays the image.
