<subsection xml:id="subsec-code-air">
  <title>Code</title>
  <term>Source code</term>
  <program>
int redLed = 8;//declaring led1
int greenLed = 12;//declaring led2
int buzzer = 10; //declaring buzzer
int smokeA0 = A0; //declaring MQ135
int sensorThres = 150; // Your threshold value
void setup() {
pinMode(redLed, OUTPUT);//mode declaration for led1
pinMode(greenLed, OUTPUT); //mode declaration for led2
pinMode(buzzer, OUTPUT);// mode declaration for buzzer
pinMode(smokeA0, INPUT);// mode declaration for MQ135
Serial.begin(9600);// Initializing serial monitor 
}
void loop() {
int analogSensor = analogRead(smokeA0);//
Serial.print("Pin A0: ");//print the value of A0
Serial.println(analogSensor);
if (analogSensor > sensorThres)// Checks if it has reached the threshold value
{
digitalWrite(redLed, HIGH);//set the Led1 to HIGH
digitalWrite(greenLed, LOW);// set the Led2 to LOW
tone(buzzer, 1000, 300);// set the buzzer to HIGH
}
else
{
  digitalWrite(redLed, LOW); set the Led1 to LOW
  digitalWrite(greenLed, HIGH); set the Led1 to HIGH
  noTone(buzzer); set the buzzer to LOW
  delay(1000);
  }
  delay(100);
  }  
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation </term>
  <ol> 
    <li>
      <p>
        The variable A0 is declared as an int variable smoke.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The int variable greenled is assigned to the 12th pin of the Arduino.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The int variable red led is assigned to 8th pin of the Arduino.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The int variable buzzer is connected to 10th  pin of the of the Arduino is assigned to 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The certain threshold is fixed as 150 int threshold =150 globally.  
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void setup() the input and output pins are declared respectively using PinMode() function.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The redLED ,greenLED and buzzer is declared as input, value from the smoke sensor is declared as smokeA0 which is considered as output variable. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Serial. Begin(9600)  function will initialize the serial monitor in ready state to send and receive the data from the Arduino to computer.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void loop function, analogread function is used to convert the digital value from the smoke sensor to analog value, to int analog sensor variable.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Using if statement when the value obtained from the sensor is greater than 150 , the redLED will set to high , buzzer will be set at tone(buzzer, 1000, 300), to indicate the risk in the quality of air.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The green LED will be set to low when the obtained value is lower than the threshold value. The output will also be displayed in the figure.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
